===Etymology===
{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} considers connection to {{cog|tai-pro|*plaːᴬ||[[fish]]}} to be unlikely.

{{zh-ref|Norman (2014)}} compares it to {{w|Kam–Tai languages|Proto-Kam-Tai}} {{m|und|*mbləi||carp}}, suggesting that it may be an early loan from Chinese; compare {{cog|th|ปลาไน|ปลา'''ไน'''|common carp}}, {{cog|lbc|tr=-plai⁴|t=carp}}.

It is also compared to {{cog|hmx-pro|*mbrəuˣ}}, which {{zh-ref|Baxter & Sagart (2014)}} consider to be a borrowing from Chinese into Hmong-Mien, while {{zh-ref|Jacques (2022b)}} contends for the reverse loan direction from {{bor|zh|hmx-pro|-}} into Chinese.

See the entry {{zh-l|*雙鯉魚}} for the figurative senses.

